commit_message:
Fixed visibility parameter for create package glare call

When creating a murano-package artifact in Glare muranoclient was not
properly passing the visibility parameter. Instead, it was passing the
'is_public' parameter, which is not supported by Glare.

Appropriate conversion has been added to PackageManagerAdapter class

Change-Id: Ia3a038d2b16e27effd208f5e4877f1f06d8ad882
Closes-bug: #1537018

commit_message:
pci: changing the claiming and allocation logic for PF/VF assignment

Claiming and allocation logic of the pci devices will be changed to
reflect the relationship between VFs and PFs.

PFs cannot be claimed or assigned if one of it's dependent VFs is
not available. As well as, all of the dependent VFs should become
UNAVAILABLE when the PF is successfully claimed/assigned.

In the same way, VF cannot be claimed or assigned when it's related
PF is assigned. In case of a successful claim/assignment of a VF,
the PF should become UNAVAILABLE.

In general, all virtual function object should disappear from PCI
and be removed from the stats, when PF is assigned. The above logic
will serve as a precaution step.

Partially implements blueprint sriov-physical-function-passthrough

Change-Id: Iae62126a8471f3b8c7a35db39d960e3bed5a1390

commit_message:
pci: store context when creating pci devices

Since Physical Functions are pemitted for pci passthrough, some
operations will require an access to a database to retrive the
parent or the dependents of a pci device.

An access to a database requires a context, which in not always
stored in the pci device object. Only those devices that has been
created from a database entry will have a stored context, while
the newly created wont.

Modifying the pci device object create method to store context.

Partially implements blueprint sriov-physical-function-passthrough

Change-Id: If81c74cb7893d7b063c5eb5c22b2a46bd6859ce6

commit_message:
Always cache tokens in a shared memcache

Instead of using in-process caching for tokens per service per
worker (disabled by default now), use a shared memcache to cache
token validation(s). This should both offload/speedup validations
and avoid the issues surrounding inconsistent validation responses
when using in-process caching [since each worker caches separately].

Conflicts:
    files/debs/keystone
    files/rpms/keystone

Change-Id: Ifc17c27744dac5ad55e84752ca6f68169c2f5a86
(cherry picked from commit afd84acd0313ff6edde0cc7a6bc7c3e0bab7ac8c)

commit_message:
Decode output of subprocess.Popen as UTF-8

Some non-ascii characters make the reading of the command's output
break. Such as the result of an error in "ln -s". So decoding to UTF-8
fixes the issue.

Change-Id: I1e5d92d36b0581c1673b413281013de59d081d9c

commit_message:
libvirt: parse live migration flags at startup

It doesn't make sense to convert the config string to a logical sum
during every live migration operation. Let's do it once at startup.

Note: this also happens during a SIGHUP-triggered reset, since the
init_host() method is called in that case.

Change-Id: I46af5260b379fcad6f39a4f1b988ae3d46fdf440
Signed-off-by: Mark McLoughlin <markmc@redhat.com>

commit_message:
network: Don't repopulate instance info cache from Neutron ports

Allocation of network interfaces for an instance can result in
corruption of the instance info cache. The result is that the cache
may contain duplicate entries for network interfaces. This can cause
instance boot failure. This bug appears to be attributable to the
combined effects of the fixes for bugs #1467581 and #1407664.

This change reverts the fix for bug #1407664, whilst keeping a
modified version of the unit test that was added with it. It also
adds a second unit test.

Change-Id: I53d5284907d44ae8b5546993f8fd461b385c39e6
Closes-bug: #1501735
Related-bug: #1467581
Related-bug: #1407664

commit_message:
Updated and new functional tests for "Network node group" test group.

    Updated tests:
    1.  T2199275: Deletion of node network group
    2.  T2199277: Renaming of node network group (Default and non-default)
    Added tests:
    1.  T2199279: Check that "Default" node network group is always the first in a list
    2.  T2199281: Deletion of several node network groups one after another
    3.  T2199282: Check that user can not create node network group with name of already existing group
    4.  T2199283: Check that user can not create node network group if there are no saved changes
    5.  T2199284: Check that user can switch between node network groups even is there are no saved changes
    6.  T2199286: Check that gateways appear for each network if there are two or more node network groups (Neutron tunneling segmentation)
    7.  T2199288: Check that the same VLAN tag can be used in different node network groups (Neutron VLAN segmentation)
    8.  T2199289: Check that the same VLAN tag can be used in different node network groups (Neutron tunneling segmentation)
    9.  T2204158: Check that user can add new node network group after deployment
    10. T2204159: Check that user can not rename new node network group after deployment
    11. T2218949: Check validation for Floating IP range when there are non-default node network group with other CIDR configuration
    12. T2351292: Check validation between default and non-default node network groups

commit_message:
Updated and new functional tests for "GUI support for Ironic" test group.

Updated tests:
1. T2199259: Enabling Ironic when create environment
2. T2199263: Check that "Ironic" item is selected on "Settings" tab
Added tests:
1. T2199264: Baremetal Network "IP Ranges" correct changing
2. T2199265: Baremetal Network "IP Ranges" adding and deletion additional fields
3. T2199266: Baremetal and other networks intersections
4. T2199267: Baremetal Network "Use the whole CIDR" option works
5. T2199268: Baremetal Network "Use VLAN tagging" option works
6. T2199269: Baremetal Network "Use VLAN tagging" option validation
7. T2199271: Baremetal Network "CIDR" field validation

Updated common.js library to prevent cluster deletion error via test failure.
Updated networks.js library by new functions for new tests.
Attention! Tests T2199266, T2199269 are need to be uncommented after bugfix.
https://bugs.launchpad.net/fuel/+bug/1517445
https://bugs.launchpad.net/fuel/+bug/1529208

commit_message:
neutron: enable MTU advertisement

This is needed if you want to run devstack using tunnelling for tenant
networks as well as multiple nodes. In this case, packets get additional
encapsulation header, and if packets are of physical device mtu size,
tunnelled data can be dropped, especially when "Dont Fragment" (DF) flag
is set.

MTU is currently advertised using DHCP option only. It works as long as
guests know how to handle it. (Cirros honors the option as of 0.3.4).

Note this patch is Liberty only. For Mitaka, we plan to change the
default value for the option to True (see the dependency). We won't be
able to backport the neutron patch to stable release since it violates
stable maintenance rules.

Change-Id: I53c0a29438d0d6433efd4b379bc0391a69d26589
Depends-On: I5cbbc4660f8c4e15e59f8f5ce0419501bdd27348
Related-Bug: #1527675

commit_message:
ServerGroupsV213SampleJsonTest should actually test v2.13

This API samples test was not using testscenarios properly,
and it wasn't extending the correct test class, so it was:

1. Not actually running tests.
2. Not running tests at the correct microversion (v2.13).

This fixes the testscenarios setup for the subclass and the
API samples and templates (since it's not using subs for the
intended project_id that was in the samples).

Also fixes a typo in ApiSampleTestBaseV21.

Change-Id: I27e8fce5d456914d88098c6cfabe05fa8afbc8eb
Closes-Bug: #1534354

commit_message:
Use of six.PY3 should be forward compatible

Care should be taken in using a condition like so:
if six.PY3:
  foo()
else:
  bar()

This assumes PY2 and PY4 would behave the same.  Rather the
conditional should check for PY2 and use the else for PY3 and
future versions of Python.

http://astrofrog.github.io/blog/2016/01/12/stop-writing-python-4-incompatible-code/

commit_message:
Fix action list icon use and spacing

The Icon used for delete actions was inconsistent with the rest
of the application. Also the lack of whitespace between icon
and text mean the rendering was quite compressed and ugly.

The alignment of the text button and drop-down button was broken
due to both having "pull-right" which has been fixed.

There is no need to have a bare <span class="fa"> here, it
serves no rendering purpose. Nor the doubling up of btn-default
and btn-danger in actions-delete-selected template.

I removed the elements of unit testing that enforced a specific
styling in the templates, as that is unnecessary and potentially
burdensome to future developers wishing to change the styling.

I removed the "btn-sm" class that was unncessary at least
in default theme under Chrome, and if sizing is actually desired
then it may be achieved through other means (a mixin or scss @extend).

Change-Id: I17ff3463aeea9ab98928124bdb0c14e82f5b04ae
Closes-Bug: 1526054

commit_message:
Make the rally job experimental

This job has not progressed significantly in the time it's existed
and remains relatively uninteresting, the results vary quite a bit
depending on the cloud/node it is running on.

The move to experimental means that it can still be triggered
manually if desired, but removing this will free resources for
other interesting check/gate jobs.

Change-Id: I30fa34cf7685bc3a81ecfd796816ab945af17b1b

commit_message:
DRAC: switch to python-dracclient on vendor-passthru

DRAC specific code from Ironic is moving to its own project, to
python-dracclient project. This patch continues refactoring code in
Ironic to use the new library.

Note that this is a backwards incompatible change. In addition to the
dependency change, return values of the following methods changed in
ironic.drivers.modules.drac.vendor_passthru:
- set_bios_config returns the 'commit_required' key
- commit_bios_config returns the 'job_id' and 'reboot_required' keys
- abandon_bios_config returns nothing

Change-Id: Iaa4cee0dae8980817803ca55cdb53789b4051bc2
Partial-Bug: #1454492
Depends-On: I574696e460f08cececc47a69b5c2b090a6cd44a2

commit_message:
Added a variable so pkg-locations to be redefined

This change adds a variable to the repo-build.yml play so that
a deployer can redefine the locations for roles and user_variables.
This is useful for downstream deployers whom may not co-locate their
roles within the OSA deployment repository, the default Ansible role
directory, or within the /etc/openstack_deploy configuration directory.

Change-Id: I4a470536203da2b2da18adf1b436503a77b75ce9
Signed-off-by: Kevin Carter <kevin.carter@rackspace.com>

commit_message:
puppet/bundle: retry failed network or git requests

Puppet OpenStack is having quite often some bundle issues when pulling
gems from rubygems servers.
Sometimes it's due to random timeouts or git failures.

This patch aims to add a retry when running 'bundle install', like it's
already done for some other jobs.

Change-Id: I51e9456e473c821607071ce9e10af76a72f553a5

commit_message:
Functional testing interface

This patch introduces a single entry point for
starting/stopping nailgun server when needed.
This could be used while running functional tests.
For example, python-fuelclient needs nailgun
to be started before running tests that send
requests to nailgun REST API.

Change-Id: I4d9954e257aec3d66b508d13500aa9204059026b
Related-Bug: #1517408

commit_message:
Change order of packages which are filterred by search
Previously, when filter by parameter 'search',
list packages which any attrribute include any key,
but ignore the  priority of attributes of the package
With this change, list packages which specified attributes include any key,
and order the packages according the specified attributes
Such as API /catalog/packages?search=mysql:name;tags,
the packages which attribute 'name' include 'mysql' are ahead of
others which only attribute 'tags' include 'mysql'

Change-Id: I575bd72f08a7fdfec4806603fa9531f6910520ba
Closes-Bug:1467487

commit_message:
Fix HAProxy config docs

The HAProxy configuration doesn't appear in openstack_user_config.yml
and the example file in the conf.d directory isn't well documented.
This documentation patch alerts deployers to the example configuration
file and tells them how to activate/configure it.

Closes-Bug: 1535874

This will require a db (consul/zk) setup for the ci testing.
To pass the full stack testing, change it to local.

commit_message:
Move pip pinning to test reqs

Adding pip to requirements.txt causes nailgun to fail on systems where
pip is not installed.

Move pip to test-requirements.txt so it doesn't affect the application.

commit_message:
Remove python-kollaclient from Kolla deliverables

As announced on the mailing list, the developers that contributed
the CLI codebase have decided to abandon their work and wait for
a fully integrated Ansible + Mesos solution before committing to
any further CLI development.  As such we are not merging this
repository and removing it as a deliverable.

When booting from ipxe in uefi boot mode, once the node boots with deploy
image, ironic is not changing the default menu entry to boot_partition
to boot the instance image during next boot. The current changes fix
the issue. The kernel parameter "initrd=ramdisk" is also added to the ipxe

Change-Id: Idf78195d228b4861f85fbcae9a269edd95523ad7
'}]
commit_message:
Fix issues with uefi-ipxe booting

When booting from ipxe in uefi boot mode, once the node boots with deploy
image, ironic is not changing the default menu entry to boot_partition
to boot the instance image during next boot. The current changes fix
the issue. The kernel parameter "initrd=ramdisk" is also added to the ipxe
template which is required for ipxe booting.

Closes-Bug: #1532679
Change-Id: Idf78195d228b4861f85fbcae9a269edd95523ad7

commit_message:
Refactored existing tempest API tests

We must set up Tempest for Watcher
(http://docs.openstack.org/developer/tempest/configuration.html)
to run integration tests inside devstack environment.

This patchset is a refactoring of the stale Tempest tests to now
use the latest Tempest coding standards (like using plugins and
credentials factory).

This commit will have an effect on the doc as we need to integrate
Tempest in the Watcher documentation.

DocImpact
Partially Implements: blueprint tempest-basic-set-up
Change-Id: I7600ff8a28d524b56c7dd4903ac4d203634ae412

commit_message:
Renamed Status to State

As we can see in the codebase, we have 3 "Status" enums which are
located at:

- watcher/objects/action.py
- watcher/objects/action_plan.py
- watcher/objects/audit.py

So I renamed them from "Status" to "State" to be consistent with
the DB schema.

Change-Id: If3d180c9daba6ae9083775ad6813aa4c21763dbf
Closes-Bug: #1522733

commit_message:
Implement VIF binding mechanism for kuryr

This patch add NetworkDriver.Join with actual neutron call

Following change is implemented:
1. Used pyroute2 NetLink library
2. Create veth pair
3. Implement ovs & midonet exec in seperate folder
   /usr/libexec/kuryr/binding/ovs.sh
   /usr/libexec/kuryr/binding/midonet.sh

Change-Id: Idcb757706d92a84d329218c7529646351b992d0a
Partially implements blueprint vif-binding-and-unbinding-mechanism
